HEADWORD: Dentifrice
<hw>Den"ti*frice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dentifricium</ets>; <ets>dens</ets>, <ets>dentis</ets>, tooth +
<ets>fricare</ets> to rub: cf. F. <ets>dentifrice</ets>. See
<er>Tooth</er>, and <er>Friction</er>.]</ety> <def>A powder or other
substance to be used in cleaning the teeth; tooth powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

